            <h3>A bit about Unison, for the uninitiated</h3>

            <p>
              Unison is a general-purpose, statically typed functional programming
              language in which functions are saved and identified by a hash of
              their AST, not as text values on a file system.
              <a href="https://www.unison-lang.org/docs/the-big-idea/">
                We think this decision has radical consequences
              </a>
              and built everything from <a href="https://share.unison-lang.org/">
                our code hosting tooling
              </a> and <a href="https://www.unison.cloud/">cloud platform</a>
              to suit this new programming model. üòé
            </p>

